args:
As the prince processes all he has learned,
androids attack and his allies appear to assist.
His friends' encouraging words remind him of
the bonds they all share, and he composes
himself and plunges headlong into the fray.
(My body comes from the Other's flesh.)
(I believed I was part of Alberian royalty,\nthe son of a great father.)
(And surrounded as I was by esteemed\nbrothers and sisters, I came to hope that\nI could somehow help the people.)
(Then I met my trusted allies and friends,\nwithout whom I would not have survived.)
(I wanted to return us to a peaceful world\nand rescue Zethia, which is why I fought\nDyrenell and the Other.)
(It seems those rumors were closer\nto the mark than I'd care to admit.)

So if there was a vessel more suited to
housing my soul—perhaps one that held
free control over dragons—I would not be
particular about holding onto the Auspex.
(I wonder if Morsayati wanted my body\nbecause I contain part of his.)
(If this were to become public knowledge,\nthe royal family would lose the people's\nhearts and be forever stained.)
(I only want peace, yet pursuing it might\nend up causing heartache for everyone.)
Androids! So they're still after me...
Damn. I've got no choice but to try and\nhold out against their assault!
Urk! Now they're behind me!\nI'm not going to be able to hold out!
Get it together, dude! You're wide open!
I'm fine, thanks to the two of you.
You need to TALK to us, man!
I mean, it's not like your thoughts aren't\na total open book to us or anything.

I'll bet my best strawberry that you're all,
＂I don't want to be trouble for everyone, 
so I guess I'll just go live in the woods
like a big fat chump!＂
I suppose you're not too far off.
Okay, so I have never—like, not ONCE—\nthought of you as a bother.

I mean, yeah, I learned a whole bunch of
stuff about my childhood in the last couple
hours that I'm still processing, but that's
fine, you know?
'Cause without coming to Alberia,\nI never would've met you guys!
And the time we spent together is pretty\nmuch my favorite time of my LIFE.
So until we have to say the big final\ngoodbye, you're just stuck with me!
We're gonna get Zethia back, and then\nthe three of us are gonna go bonkers\ntraveling all over this world!
We'll eat all kinds of foods and talk about\nall sorts of things and just...do whatever!
I was meant to keep an eye on you,\nand by cake I AM GONNA DO IT!
I'm certain Zethia feels the same.
Time flows not from past to future,\nbut from the future to the past.
Or at least, that's what I now believe\nhaving traveled numerous worlds.
What's important is not changing incidents\nin the past, but changing what they MEAN.
And the path you travel now will give you\nthe ability to shine whatever light you\nwant on your own past.
So lift your head and think about\nwhat is to come.
It took some time to track you down.
Rest easy, Your Majesty. We shall be your\nshield and protect you unto the end.
Yeah, we're gonna turn these androids\ninto an-DUDs! ...Okay, that didn't work.\nBut you get what I mean!
All right everyone, let's do this!
